#: R/mui.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>*p<0.05</b> - The hypothesis of normal distribution was rejected by the "
"Shapiro-Wilk test"
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Allele frequencies (p, q)</b> represent the proportions of the two "
"alleles in the sample. For a biallelic marker with alleles A and B: p = "
"freq(A) = (2*n_AA + n_AB) / (2*N), q = 1 - p."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Allelic test</b> compares allele frequencies between case and control "
"groups using a 2×2 contingency table. Tests whether the minor allele is "
"significantly more (or less) frequent in cases than controls."
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Alpha (α)</b> is the significance level, representing the maximum "
"acceptable probability of committing a Type I error (detecting a false "
"positive difference when none actually exists)."
msgstr ""

#: R/mui.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Balance</b> - balance between correctly and incorrectly classified cases "
"(TP+TN)/(FP+FN)"
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Balanced Accuracy (BA)</b> = (Sensitivity + Specificity) / 2. Accounts "
"for class imbalance. BA = 0.5 indicates random classification."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Best model selection</b>: the genetic model with the lowest p-value (or "
"AIC/BIC) is highlighted. This helps identify the most likely mode of "
"inheritance for the observed association."
msgstr ""

#: R/mcor.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>BETWEENNESS</b>: number of shortest paths between all pairs of nodes that "
"pass through this node; shows its importance as a \"bridge\" or transit "
"point."
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid "<b>Calculated parameter</b>:"
msgstr ""

#: R/mui.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>CCR</b> - Correct Classification Rate or accuracy of the positive and "
"negative classifications (TP+TN)/(TN+FP+FN+TP)"
msgstr ""

#: R/mcor.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Centrality metrics</b> (different measures of a node's importance in the "
"network)."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Chi-square test</b> is the classical Pearson goodness-of-fit test "
"comparing observed and expected genotype counts under HWE. Suitable for "
"large sample sizes (N > 50). Asymptotic; may be unreliable for rare alleles."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Classification</b> defines the epistatic model: subjects in HR cells are "
"predicted as cases, LR cells as controls."
msgstr ""

#: R/mcor.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>CLOSENESS</b>: inverse of the sum of shortest path lengths to all other "
"nodes; shows how central a node is in terms of distance."
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Clusters (k1/k2)</b> represent the required number of clusters (e.g., "
"clinics or schools) per group. This is adjusted for similarity among "
"subjects within the same cluster using the Intraclass Correlation "
"Coefficient (<b>ICC</b>) and average cluster size via the Design Effect."
msgstr ""

#: R/mui.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Concordance</b> - C-Statistic or AUC. The probability that a randomly "
"chosen subject with the condition is correctly ranked higher than a randomly "
"chosen subject without the condition"
msgstr ""

#: R/mcor.b.R
msgid "<b>Correlation method</b>: {method}"
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Cross-Validation Consistency (CVC)</b> is the number of folds (out of K) "
"in which the model was selected as best. Higher CVC indicates greater "
"stability of the identified interaction."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>D' (normalized LD)</b> measures the strength of linkage disequilibrium "
"between two loci, scaled to [-1, 1]. <b>|D'| = 1</b> indicates complete LD "
"(no recombination observed), <b>D' = 0</b> indicates linkage equilibrium "
"(independent assortment)."
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid "<b>Design</b>:"
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid "<b>Effect size measure</b>: Cohen's d"
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid "<b>Effect size measure</b>: Cohen's w"
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid "<b>Effect size measure</b>: correlation coefficient (r)"
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid "<b>Effect size measure</b>: Eta-squared (η²)"
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid "<b>Effect size measure</b>: Hazard Ratio (HR)"
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid "<b>Effect size measure</b>: Odds Ratio"
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid "<b>Effect size measure</b>: R-squared change (f²)"
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Effect Size</b> measures the standardized magnitude of the difference or "
"association (e.g., Cohen's d for means, or correlation coefficient). Unlike "
"p-values, it is independent of the sample size."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Effective number of alleles (Ne)</b> is the reciprocal of homozygosity: "
"Ne = 1 / Σ(pi²). Ne = 1 indicates fixation (monomorphic), Ne = 2 indicates "
"equal allele frequencies for a biallelic marker."
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Events (N1)</b> represents the required number of target events (e.g., "
"deaths or failures) to achieve the desired power. In survival analysis, "
"statistical power is driven by the number of events rather than the total "
"number of subjects."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Exact test</b> (Haldane, 1954) computes the exact probability of the "
"observed heterozygote count, conditional on the allele counts. Recommended "
"for small samples or rare alleles."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Expected genotype frequencies</b> are the counts predicted under "
"Hardy-Weinberg equilibrium: E(AA) = p² × N, E(AB) = 2pq × N, E(BB) = q² × N."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Expected heterozygosity (H_exp)</b> is the heterozygosity expected under "
"HWE: H_exp = 2pq. A significant difference between H_obs and H_exp may "
"indicate inbreeding, population substructure, or selection."
msgstr ""

#: R/mcor.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>EXPECTED INFLUENCE</b>: sum of signed weights of connected edges; shows "
"the node's net impact on the network, considering positive and negative "
"relations."
msgstr ""

#: R/mmf.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Explanatory</b> - variable corresponding to MAR with minimal "
"p<sub>value</sub>."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Genetic models</b> test the association under different inheritance "
"patterns: <b>Codominant</b> (AA vs AB vs BB), <b>Dominant</b> (AA vs AB+BB), "
"<b>Recessive</b> (AA+AB vs BB), <b>Overdominant</b> (AA+BB vs AB), "
"<b>Log-additive</b> (trend test for allele dose 0/1/2)."
msgstr ""

#: R/mcor.b.R
msgid "<b>Hₐ</b> is negative correlation"
msgstr ""

#: R/mcor.b.R
msgid "<b>Hₐ</b> is positive correlation"
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Haplotype frequencies</b> are estimated using the "
"Expectation-Maximization (EM) algorithm from unphased genotype data. The "
"p-value tests the null hypothesis D = 0 (linkage equilibrium)."
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Hazard Ratio (HR)</b> represents the ratio of event rates between the two "
"groups. A Hazard Ratio of 1 indicates no difference in risk, while values "
"further from 1 represent stronger effects."
msgstr ""

#: R/msrv.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Hazard Ratio (HR)</b> represents the ratio of the hazard rates "
"corresponding to the conditions described by two levels of an explanatory "
"variable (Cox, 1972). It indicates the relative risk of event occurrence per "
"unit change in the predictor. An <b>HR > 1</b> indicates an increased hazard "
"(higher risk of the event), while an <b>HR < 1</b> indicates a decreased "
"hazard (protective effect). <b>Lower/Upper 95% CI</b> represent the "
"confidence interval for the Hazard Ratio."
msgstr ""

#: R/mmlp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Hidden Layers</b>: network architecture (hidden layer sizes, hidden / "
"output activation functions)"
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>High-Risk (HR)</b> cells have cases/controls ratio ≥ threshold T. "
"<b>Low-Risk (LR)</b> cells have ratio < T."
msgstr ""

#: R/mmlp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Hold-out Accuracy</b>: classification accuracy on the hold-out validation "
"dataset."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Inbreeding coefficient (F_IS)</b> measures deviation from HWE: F_IS = 1 - "
"H_obs / H_exp. <b>F_IS > 0</b> indicates heterozygote deficiency "
"(inbreeding), <b>F_IS < 0</b> indicates heterozygote excess (outbreeding), "
"<b>F_IS = 0</b> indicates Hardy-Weinberg equilibrium."
msgstr ""

#: R/mmlp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>K-Fold CV Accuracy</b>: average classification accuracy across "
"cross-validation folds."
msgstr ""

#: R/msrv.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Kaplan-Meier estimator</b> (Kaplan & Meier, 1958) is a non-parametric "
"statistic used to estimate the survival function from lifetime data, "
"accounting for censored observations. <b>Median survival</b> is the "
"estimated time at which 50% of the subjects have experienced the event "
"(survival probability drops to 0.5). <b>Lower/Upper 95% CI</b> represent the "
"95% confidence interval limits for this median survival time."
msgstr ""

#: R/msrv.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Likelihood Ratio</b>, <b>Wald</b>, and <b>Score (Log-rank)</b> tests "
"assess the global null hypothesis that all regression coefficients (beta) in "
"the model are equal to zero. Statistically significant p-values (p < 0.05) "
"indicate that the predictors collectively improve the model fit relative to "
"a null model without covariates."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Likelihood-ratio test</b> compares the likelihood of the data under HWE "
"versus the saturated model. The test statistic -2 × ln(L_HWE / L_sat) "
"follows chi-square with 1 df."
msgstr ""

#: R/msrv.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Log-rank (Mantel-Cox) test</b> is a non-parametric hypothesis test that "
"compares the survival distributions of two or more independent groups. It "
"evaluates the null hypothesis that there is no difference in survival curves "
"between groups. <b>Chi-square</b> is the test statistic based on observed "
"vs. expected events, and the <b>p-value</b> indicates the statistical "
"significance of the differences under the null hypothesis."
msgstr ""

#: R/mui.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>LR-</b> - Negative Likelihood Ratio (P(-|D+))/(P(-|D-)). The ratio of the "
"probability of a person with the condition receiving a negative "
"classification to the probability of a person without the condition "
"receiving a negative classification"
msgstr ""

#: R/mui.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>LR+</b> - Positive Likelihood Ratio (P(+|D+))/(P(+|D-)). The ratio of the "
"probability of a person with the condition receiving a positive "
"classification to the probability of a person without the condition "
"receiving a positive classification"
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>MAF (Minor Allele Frequency)</b> is the frequency of the less common "
"allele in the population. Markers with <b>MAF < 0.01</b> are typically "
"considered monomorphic and may be excluded from analysis. <b>MAF < 0.05</b> "
"indicates a rare variant."
msgstr ""

#: R/mmf.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>MAR</b> - missing at random (if each p<sub>value</sub> is significant, "
"there is evidence the data is MAR);"
msgstr ""

#: R/mmlp.b.R
msgid "<b>Max Iterations</b>: maximum number of training epochs."
msgstr ""

#: R/mmf.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>MCAR</b> - missing completely at random (if the p<sub>value</sub> is not "
"significant, there is evidence the data is MCAR)."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>MDR (Multifactor Dimensionality Reduction)</b> (Ritchie et al., 2001) is "
"a non-parametric method for detecting gene-gene interactions (epistasis). It "
"reduces high-dimensional genotype combinations into a binary variable "
"(high-risk vs. low-risk)."
msgstr ""

#: R/mcor.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Method</b>: Classical Partial Correlation (no regularization/L1 penalty). "
"Computes the linear association between each pair of variables while "
"controlling for all other variables in the dataset, producing a fully "
"connected network."
msgstr ""

#: R/mcor.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Method</b>: Classical Semi-Partial Correlation (no regularization/L1 "
"penalty). Computes the linear association between each pair of variables "
"while controlling for all other variables in the dataset from only the "
"second variable, yielding an asymmetric network."
msgstr ""

#: R/mcor.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Method</b>: Graphical Lasso (GLASSO) with a manual penalty parameter (rho "
"= {rho}). GLASSO uses L1 regularization to shrink weak partial correlations "
"to exactly zero, producing a sparse network."
msgstr ""

#: R/mcor.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Method</b>: Graphical Lasso (GLASSO) with Extended Bayesian Information "
"Criterion (EBIC) tuning parameter selection (gamma = {gamma}). GLASSO uses "
"L1 regularization to shrink weak partial correlations to exactly zero, "
"producing a sparse network."
msgstr ""

#: R/mui.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>More Certain Interval (MCI)</b> is the interval outside the Uncertain "
"Interval and is divided into low and high parts."
msgstr ""

#: R/mmf.b.R
msgid "<b>MSE</b> - mean squared error (for Continuous variables);"
msgstr ""

#: R/mmf.b.R
msgid "<b>N</b> - number of missing values;"
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>N1</b> and <b>N2</b> represent the required number of subjects in Group 1 "
"and Group 2. The ratio of their sizes is determined by the specified "
"allocation ratio."
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>N1</b> represents the required sample size (total number of subjects in "
"the single group, or total number of pairs for paired comparisons)."
msgstr ""

#: R/mui.b.R
msgid "<b>NPV</b> - Negative Predictive Value of the negative class TN/(TN+FN)"
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Observed genotype frequencies</b> are the raw counts and proportions of "
"each genotype (AA, AB, BB) directly from the data."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Observed heterozygosity (H_obs)</b> is the proportion of heterozygous "
"individuals (AB) in the sample: H_obs = n_AB / N."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Odds Ratio (OR)</b> quantifies the strength of association between an "
"allele/genotype and the outcome. <b>OR > 1</b> indicates increased risk, "
"<b>OR < 1</b> indicates protective effect, <b>OR = 1</b> indicates no "
"association. The 95% CI that does not cross 1.0 indicates significance."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>p-adjusted</b> is the p-value corrected for multiple testing across "
"markers using the selected method (Bonferroni, Holm, or Benjamini–Hochberg "
"FDR)."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Permutation p-value</b> is obtained by shuffling outcome labels. It "
"represents the proportion of permuted datasets that achieved a testing BA ≥ "
"the observed value."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Permutation test</b> estimates the p-value by randomly permuting alleles "
"among genotypes. Distribution-free; valid for any sample size."
msgstr ""

#: R/mmf.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>PFC</b> - proportion of falsely classified (for Nominal and Ordinal "
"variables);"
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>PIC (Polymorphism Information Content)</b> measures the informativeness "
"of a genetic marker. <b>PIC > 0.5</b> is highly informative, <b>0.25 < PIC < "
"0.5</b> is moderately informative, <b>PIC < 0.25</b> is slightly informative "
"(Botstein et al., 1980)."
msgstr ""

#: R/mpwr.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Power</b> is the probability of correctly detecting a statistically "
"significant difference when a true difference exists in the population (1 - "
"Type II error rate, or the probability of avoiding a false negative)."
msgstr ""

#: R/mui.b.R
msgid "<b>PPV</b> - Positive Predictive Value of the positive class TP/(TP+FP)"
msgstr ""

#: R/mmf.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>PVU</b> - proportion of variance unexplained 1-R² (for Continuous "
"variables);"
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>r² (squared correlation)</b> measures both LD strength and allele "
"frequency similarity. <b>r² = 1</b> indicates perfect LD (complete mutual "
"predictability), <b>r² > 0.8</b> is commonly used as the threshold for "
"strong LD in GWAS tag-SNP selection. r² is preferred over D' for association "
"study design because it directly relates to statistical power."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Ratio</b> = Cases / Controls. Empty cells (no observations) are left "
"unclassified."
msgstr ""

#: R/msrv.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Schoenfeld residuals test</b> evaluates the proportional hazards (PH) "
"assumption of the Cox model for each covariate individually and globally. It "
"tests whether the effect of the covariates is constant over time. A "
"statistically significant <b>p-value (p < 0.05)</b> indicates a violation of "
"the PH assumption, meaning the hazard ratio changes over time."
msgstr ""

#: R/mui.b.R
msgid "<b>Se</b> - sensitivity of the positive class TP/(TP+FN)"
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Shannon Information Index (I)</b> quantifies allelic diversity. Higher "
"values indicate greater diversity. For a biallelic marker, maximum I = ln(2) "
"≈ 0.693 when allele frequencies are equal."
msgstr ""

#: R/mui.b.R
msgid "<b>SNPV</b> - standardized negative predictive value of the negative class"
msgstr ""

#: R/mui.b.R
msgid "<b>Sp</b> - specificity of the negative class TN/(TN+FP)"
msgstr ""

#: R/mui.b.R
msgid "<b>SPPV</b> - standardized positive predictive value of the positive class"
msgstr ""

#: R/mcor.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>STRENGTH</b>: sum of absolute weights of connected edges; shows how "
"strongly a node is directly connected to its neighbors."
msgstr ""

#: R/msrv.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Time-dependent ROC</b> analysis (Heagerty et al., 2000) evaluates the "
"predictive accuracy of continuous markers for time-to-event outcomes at a "
"specific time point <i>t</i>, classifying patients into event-occurring or "
"event-free states. <b>AUC</b> (Area Under the Curve) measures the "
"discriminative ability (ranging from 0.5 to 1.0). <b>Cut-off</b> represents "
"the optimal threshold determined by the Youden index (J = Sensitivity + "
"Specificity - 1)."
msgstr ""

#: R/mmlp.b.R
msgid "<b>Training Accuracy</b>: classification accuracy on the training dataset."
msgstr ""

#: R/msnp.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Training BA</b> may be optimistically biased. <b>Testing BA</b> is "
"computed on the held-out fold and provides an unbiased estimate of "
"predictive performance."
msgstr ""

#: R/mui.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Uncertain Interval (UI)</b> is placed around the point of intersection "
"between the two distributions with and without the targeted state."
msgstr ""

#: R/mui.b.R
msgid ""
"<b>Uncertain Interval</b> is considered to be a range of test scores that is "
"inconclusive and does not warrant a right decision."
msgstr ""

#: R/mmlp.b.R
msgid "<b>Weight Decay</b>: L2 regularization penalty parameter."
msgstr ""

